The paper focuses on using natural language processing (NLP) techniques to support onboarding and retention in open source communities. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) category, which deals with the development and maintenance of software systems. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the text of issue descriptions, which falls under the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) category. The paper also touches on issues related to community management and social interaction, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) categories. Overall, the most likely category is cs.SE, followed by cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, and cs.HC.
